The paper proposes a hybrid biometric template protection approach that utilizes feature transformation techniques. Therefore, it is also likely that this paper belongs to the cs.CV sub-category.
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) - Biometric authentication systems often involve multimedia data such as images, videos, and audio recordings. The paper proposes a new random orthonormal project technique to reduce the computational complexity of the system while preserving accuracy. Therefore, it is possible that this paper belongs to the cs.MM sub-category.
